Exploratory Data Analysis Report
1. Introduction
This project analyzes customer purchasing behavior using Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) techniques.
The objective is to uncover patterns, trends, and relationships between customer age, income, and spending score.
2. Dataset Information
Dataset contains:
Customer ID
Gender
Age
Annual Income
Spending Score
Total Records: 15
3. Technologies Used
Python
Pandas
Matplotlib
Seaborn
Jupyter Notebook
4. Data Cleaning
Performed:
Missing value checking
Data validation
Statistical summaries
5. Visualizations
Correlation Heatmap
Shows relationships between:
Age
Income
Spending Score
Distribution Plot
Displays annual income distribution of customers.
Scatter Plot
Shows relationship between:
Age
Spending Score
6. Key Insights
Younger customers spend more.
Spending behavior changes with age.
Income affects spending patterns.
Female customers show slightly higher spending.
7. Conclusion
EDA helps identify customer behavior trends and supports better business decision-making using data visualization and statistical analysis.
